&gt; hi Jamie,
&gt; 
&gt; to run Heritrix1 in Eclipse:
&gt; 
&gt; - create a new project from SVN
&gt; File &gt; New &gt; Other &gt; Checkout projects from SVN
&gt; Create a new repository location:
&gt; https://archive-crawler.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/archive-crawler 
&gt; &lt;https://archive-crawler.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/archive-crawler&gt;
&gt; Select trunk/heritrix
&gt; Click Finish
&gt; 
&gt; - create a new Run Configuration
&gt; Project: heritrix
&gt; Main class: org.archive.crawler.Heritrix
&gt; Program arguments: -a user:pass
&gt; VM Arguments: -Dheritrix.development -Xmx512M
&gt; Click Run
&gt; 
&gt; - open browser to web UI at: http://localhost:8080 &lt;http://localhost:8080&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; Note: the VM argument &quot;-Dheritrix.development&quot; sets the
&gt; heritrix.development property, which helps the Heritrix
&gt; class find the admin UI webapp in a development
&gt; environment. see source for details.
&gt; 
&gt; if you are missing any jars, be sure to setup an M2_REPO
&gt; variable in Eclipse which points to your maven repository,
&gt; typically &quot;~/.m2/repository&quot;, and run mvn install (outside
&gt; of Eclipse) inside your project directory, to have the
&gt; necessary jars pulled in.
